         <div type="comments">
            <p>
               <note type="philcomment">An ornamental vertical stroke marks the left margin on the recto. A similar ornamental vertical stroke as on the recto marks the left margin of the verso; otherwise, the verso is blank, except for the leaf number.</note>
               <note type="remarks">Acording to <bibl><title corresp="ref:broomhead1962"/><citedRange>293</citedRange></bibl> "[w]ritten in small ductus and very clearly preserved it is the left hand edge of a manuscript with five lines on the recto, and no writing on the verso. The verso has the number <hi rend="underline">five</hi> on the left. The recto seems only to have been written on at the extreme left. At the end of the first line of the recto is the number <hi rend="underline">three</hi>."</note>
            </p>
